cs.HC, cs.DB, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL

This paper is about creating a large-scale corpus of datasets for visualization learning and benchmarking. The focus is on developing benchmark models and algorithms for automating visual analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), followed by Databases (cs.DB) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR) as the paper deals with compiling datasets from open data repositories. Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Computation and Language (cs.CL) are also possible categories as the paper discusses developing benchmark models and algorithms for automating visual analysis.
